<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Moan2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Moan,</orth> vb. to lament: <cit><quote>to make him m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 977" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 977</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>m. the expense of many a vanished sight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 30.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 30, 8</bibl></cit>. Some M. Edd. <emph>--s</emph> for <emph>means</emph> in <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.330" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 330</bibl>.
